# AIPM Definition of Done

Every new runtime component is **not complete** until **all** of the following pass:

1. Builds successfully (`dotnet build src/AIPM.sln -c Release`)
2. All tests pass (`dotnet test src/AIPM.sln -c Release`)
3. Architecture tests pass (`AIPM.Architecture.Tests`)
4. No analyzer warnings in CI (`TreatWarningsAsErrors` when `CI=true`)
5. `dotnet format src/AIPM.sln --verify-no-changes` passes
6. Public APIs have XML documentation comments
7. Clean Architecture dependency rules are not violated (NetArchTest)
8. No circular project references
9. Docker Compose stack still starts (`deploy/docker/docker-compose.yml`)
10. Existing milestones are not broken (no regressions)

A milestone is finished when the software **runs** and demonstrates the capability — not when a document says APPROVED.

**M2+:** No AI/LLM providers until the dummy-agent vertical slice works end-to-end.
